memories.memory:
When I was little, I’d spend hours waddling around Club Penguin, drawing art of the island and pretending I worked for the Penguin Times as a reporter. Now, somehow, I am an artist for a recreation of the game. It feels like circling back to a piece of my childhood.

 Every art piece I make now feels like a thank you letter to that kid who believed in penguins, never stopped creating, and believed in me.
Honestly I have played it since it first came out, it was such a big party of my childhood. It is just so nostalgic and easy to love.
Club Penguin allowed me to find community with others, back when I was just an anxious, shy kid. That community still lives 20 years after we first found this island, even after I've grown up.
Becoming a secret agent and encountering Herbert P. Bear. Along with this, with the DS game you could unlock the coolest room in the game, the command room!
I grew up with Club Penguin, my first online world shared with my older brother. We explored parties, met mascots, and found pins together. It’s gone now, but the memories will always stay.

Club Penguin was my comfort game through my childhood. It was there when things were bad, no matter what. I felt like I belonged waddling around with everyone on the island. Whether it was fighting Herbert with the EPF, mastering Card-Jitsu, or just talking to a friend, I felt like my presence made a difference somewhere. I'm glad a space like that can and does still exist on the internet, and that no matter how small, my little penguin affected it somehow. Waddle on you funky penguins :3
It's cozy, fun, engaging, did I say cozy? As a kid, I was heavily bullied at school, and so it was so nice to come here in an online safe space to make friends and  play games.
i love everything about it. it was my first ever online chatting game and i made so many friends on there.
Unlike most online spaces, Club Penguin felt friendly. Snow fell quietly in the background, everyone waddled around, and even the music had this soft, nostalgic charm.
Spending the day with my sister playing CP, buying different toys and the Wii game. CP was part of my life
Being able to play & chat to forget about home life. Did those family rp's & the causes they'd do that made me feel I was apart of something bigger.
I joined during 2012's Holiday Party and fell in love with the game. The rooms and sky were so festive and cheerful, and the items so cozy. It was such a fun experience.
When Game Day stamps were released, I remember my childhood friends came down with their Wii remotes to help me get the final stamp for it. I managed to get every single stamp in the original game.
I started playing in 2009 and joined the Halloween Party that year. I always played with my school friends, and every birthday I got a membership to play before my party.
The vibrant community, from elderly penguins to young pufflings!
the holidays spent with friends in the pizza parlor.
Going on the original website and seeing a party was super exciting, especially when walking in on a mascot! You'd never be told about these ahead of time so they felt extra special in the moment!
The community and everyone being so kind!
i come BACK WITH THE MEMORY OF SOME DRAGONS IDK WHAT EVENT WAS THAT BUT I REMEMBER WHEN WAS 3 DRANGOS STANDING RIGHT IN FRONT OF MY EYES AND I NEED TO TRHOW SNOWBALLS IN THEM
I started in 1st grade, I'll 20 on the 14th. My uncle helped me set up my first account, the password was Iloveyou. He passed away this year. I miss him. Thank you for being part of my childhood.
What made it special to me were the interactive mascots. Sure they were crowded, but it was fun to go around and meet the mascots from each party.
I joined Club Penguin in early 2010, and the idea of being a secret agent had me hooked. I had both DS games, and I remember feeling so important during Operation Blackout!
club penguin is my first online game ever!! i was around 5 years old when my dad introduced me to club penguin <3
Parties, roleplays, items, mascots, and friends. Favorite memories include becoming a member during the Penguin Play Awards, Operation: Blackout, and roleplaying with friends.
The community and how the devs cared about us. Fav memory was meeting Sensei in town in 2010. Its why I sit there today!
Club Penguin let me express myself as a kid when I had no where else to go. I remember playing for hours upon hours whether it was summer or after school <3
We Like All Parties And Including Operation Event.
Club Penguin felt like a warm hug from my childhood — full of laughter, imagination, and snowball fights with friends.
Still think about that one summer we played Club Penguin together. I was so happy then — I’m sorry things got complicated, and I miss you, bestie.
the psa missions, the fashion in the game, and the parties. i love being able to escape real life and just run around as a penguin.
i loved learning about the world and all the little secrets hidden in throughout the game, you could see it was a passion project 😎
My brother and I having an account each, playing together exploring, playing games, meeting Rockhopper for the first time, helping each other get to black belt in Card Jitsu
Every login felt like coming home - friends at the Pizza Parlor, parties at the Iceberg, and memories that still warm my heart.
place to make friends and have fun after school
Doing all the P.S.A missions for the first time and getting very emotionally attached to the black puffle in G's Secret Mission!
I have such fond memories of the Halloween party music. Now, there's not an October that passes by where I don't play Club Penguin Halloween music on repeat.
Club Penguin made my childhood so much fun; I never missed a beat. I used to skip whenever there's a new catalog and used dial up internet to play at my summer house!
I was alone on a quiet server in the forest when Rockhopper spawns in during the 2009 Holiday Party. He said "Har har har!" and went straight to the plaza. I felt so lucky.
All the hidden areas and mini games. It really felt like there was something for everyone, whether it was socialising and making new friends or just exploring.
Meeting the mascots around the map for signed backgrounds
club penguin was the best memory is gone but not forgotten. I remember the one time I saw penguins flip the iceberg after 12 years! we were very happy.
My sister passed away when we were teens. As kids she would sit next to me on the floor all summer, singing along to the radio while I went ice fishing as a purple penguin.
Fun Ideas the original had when pool was broken it turned into the one of the most original parties ever seen The festival of flight! hope to see it again!
Club Penguin was special to me for the community it brought - and I feel like now, we all grew up and are reigniting that joy the OG game brought us!
Making friends via mascot tracking in 2010 that I'm still in touch with 15 years later!
Club Penguin was my childhood community. I didn’t have much growing up, but there I could just be myself. Forever grateful for my home away from home. ❤️
Club Penguin marked my late 2000s, my first multiplayer memories, fun with friends, in a cozy snowy island. Playing it again brings all that joy back :)
It’s 2007. The Cove and Forest were just added to the map — new spots after ages! Summer party’s on: palm trees, duck floaties, surfing. Pure magic. Take me back!
It was such a safe and special place for children - I was always so excited to log in after school! My favourite bits were the EPF and Card Jitsu!
Parties like the superhero and EPF ones, they were amazing and so fun!
The different parts of the dojo as well as the secret agent HQ and the puffle hotel!
Under a different username my first time playing CP was when I was 6 or 7, in the EARLY 2000s, my sister and I would sit in the computer room and play for hours.
ALL the parties! It was fun to see what kind of activities each one had to offer. My favourites were the Future Party and the Fair's Amazement Park!
i played it everyday it was my favourite this one brings back memories from when i was small
Dependable. No matter what was happening in my life or the world I could always escape to Club Penguin, waddling around and making new friends ;)
